[ProMED-mail is grateful for Dr John's clarification of the use of the term AES in the reports that come to us for posting. We await with interest the publication of the Reye-like acute hypoglycemic encephalopathy report. That will help with interpretation of the Bihar state pre-monsoon reports of AES that appear in the popular press, which frequently cite statements of government officials about the occurrence of AES cases there. It would be of interest to know how many, if any, of the reported JE virus infection cases are in reality due to West Nile virus infections.

Maps of India showing the location of West Bengal, Bihar, Assam, and Arunachal Pradesh states can be accessed at http://www.mapsofindia.com/images2/india-map.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2656983,142. - Mod.TY]
